hat were going with us thinking so little of you now. Saturday morniung I asked one of yours if he would like to come and group with us. I probaly shouldn't of told him we were raiding then maybe you wouldn't of all been there an hr later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9999cc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub17.ezboard.com/ukiratano666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kiratano666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(11/23/01 1:39:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: made this clear ok?</span><hr size=1>   Hmm, i really dislike reading such threads that are insulting my guilds values and saying that we did a dishonourable act.<br>  I have been on countless raids and played EQ for over 2 years and i am proud to say that when i joined zenith sage i met some of the friendliest and fairest players that i had the pleasure of meeting in my eq life so far. Please do not judge a guild or its members by a misunderstanding of sorts, i find it to be offensive and assuming. Raids are events that cater for large amounts of people, usually people in a guild together.     Certain zones and mobs are a challenging target for guilds and the players benefit from it in many ways. They are involved in a social activity where teamwork and tactics are used to achieve ones goals, the bottom line is that it is a fun thing to do, regardless of what loots or etc is involved. Now getting on to my main point :  if what you state is true, that you place people values before loots then think about this please. I as a member of Zenith Sage am not aware of your guilds plans, i have never seen this calendar that ppl speak of, and i attend raids to have fun with my friends. If there are 40 members of ZS gathered together and are ready for an event, do you think that it is right of you guys to have 3 people stand at the zone in and claim it as yours? I dont think that it is nice or honourable to expect a full turn out of guild members leave because a few ppl are planning to go somewhere later. Do you expect a ZS officer to say to the 40 members that gathered there to log and go to sleep because another guild is going to gather their members in the next few hours? To me that doesnt make sense. This situation reminds me of a long time ago when i used to group in OS and you would have a full group ready to move to King or Chef or etc. but there would be 1 or 2 persons claiming that camp from zone in. If what u say is true, that u value people before you do loot then i think you will understand what i mean because that is exactly the way i think too. <br>  <br>Anyway, be safe and good hunting in the lands of Norrath. I am a well wishing person and all the best to Sacred Guardians. I am not sarcastic, just my plain old friendly and rational self <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    bye<br><br>Kiratano Hyperclaw<br>Grandmaster and proud member of ZSSMS (zenith sage suicide monk squad) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub17.ezboard.com/uwrowin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wrowin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(11/23/01 1:45:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: made this clear ok?</span><hr size=1> You know if you wanted to try to work something out next time rather than say we dont use your calender send a TELL.<br>I still think greed got the better of common courtesy, not VI rules, rules of human contact...you know respect your neighbor  stuff. it is apparent from your reaction you do not desire to be dishonerable so maybe take a breath next time and ask am I being greedy?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9999cc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub17.ezboard.com/ubamorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bamorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(11/23/01 1:59:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.igon.org/~bamorm/tailoring.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: made this clear ok?</span><hr size=1> You may be on limited time.. well we are on limited resources. It unfortunately does require planning for us to do raids like fear and we can't just on a whim decide lets go do CT and who cares if anyone else was trying to have some fun today.<br><br>Selfish greed rules EQ and has for a long time. <br><br>It would not have been that big a deal for you to give us a few hours to have some fun and hopefully get some of our members some gear that they would not otherwise be able to obtain. We both know that SG is not capable of killing CT so it's not like you had any reason to fear us taking him from you.<br><br>What this boils down to (and ZS are of course not the only offenders) is that the larger/higher level guilds don't remember when they were small and low level and have no respect for their fellow EQers. Fine you were shouting out loot but would you not have been complaining about there being too many players in the zone? and it would have caused you lag problems had we zone our forces in while you were trying to clear the zone and kill CT. Also the loot was only half the reason for going to fear and it would be foolish to zone in there risking death and possibly wasting your time CRing us just to sit on out butts and wait for the drops.<br><br>I feel sorry for people and guilds who think EQ is just about the loot and have no fun playing. Why bother playing if you take no joy from the game, only care about loot and step on the little guy at every opportunity to satisfy your greed?<br><br>I suggest you take a good look at TKR and TMO and learn from their example. Both those guilds have changed their ways 180 degrees and as far as I can see they are not suffering by being a bit nicer. You don't have to be assholes to do well in this game and you'll probably have a lot more fun.<br> <p>Bamorm Canisrufus, Beloved of Clarissiana Moira - 57 ShamanSacred Guardians</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub17.ezboard.com/ukiratano666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kiratano666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(11/23/01 2:04:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  a reply to Vhaevictis</span><hr size=1>   You are well spoken Vhaevictis, but i think you have misjudged the whole situation and did not talk with ZS officers because you thought we do not care. We were not there to farm armor, we have no need for it. If you guys would have talked to our officers i am sure that you could have had it all. Our target was Cazik Thule and we cannot sit down at zone in and wait for 6 or 8 hours  for you guys to clear the zone before we can go in and attempt Cazik. I think it is fair to say that u guys would not have been attempting Cazik. A final note : people do not go to the PoF for experience, i remember my early days of going to planes raids and i also remember usually losing exp. U guys wanted the armor and you could have had it without worries. If you would have attempted to communicate with ZS officers it probably would have ended up with you guild not having to kill anything just chilling out while we kill stuff and you loot all the armor you want. I wonder if you would be thinking the same of ZS in that case as you are atm. Communication is essential, and a good way to make friends and work things out. <br>    Bye <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Kiratano Hyperclaw<br>Grandmaster of Drunken style kung fu ( can i have another stack of elven fish wine and oggok swamp khalish please? hehe) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9999cc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub17.ezboard.com/ubalbanbattlefist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balban Battlefist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(11/23/01 2:45:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: a reply to Vhaevictis</span><hr size=1> I can't remember in recent history TMO, TKR, DoA, RoA or any other guild checking with us about what we are planning to kill. Do people book ToV and the first brood dragons? What about traky and the Kunark dragons? Vox or naggy? Maybe i should book ragefire?<br>If a guild kills a mob/plane that we were hoping to do we don't go complain and flame their page. We do something else.<br>I wasn't even aware the calander still exsisted.<br>I'm also pretty new to ZS but I have never witnessed them act in a rude fashion. If you were in there already killing or about to zone in we would have left and done something else. Thats the way 90% of guilds I have seen work. And us complaining about another guild TRAINING us to KILL us while we fight a mob is not even remotely comparable to this situation.<br> Kiratano is right, its rude to expect 40 people to wait and waste their time. I understand that because we have no ally guild and we have the power to move about quickly and kill what we choose that we may seem aloof and arogant, but ZS members are among the nicest people I've met in the game.<br> I have to stress and I'm not sure if you guys raid velious much. Its normaly first there with the power gets it, no disrespect to the faster guild. It sucks but thats the way verant has made it.<br><br>Balban Battlefist <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showMessageRange?topicID=157.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showMessageRange?topicID=157.topic&start=41&stop=43>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showPrevMessage?topicID=157.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showNextMessage?topicID=157.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fzenithsagepublic.emailToFriend?topicID=157.topic><img sr